DESCRIPTION:<p>Bring Your Own Binoculars and Chair! This is a guided tour i
 nto the wonders of the night sky that are visible through common binoculars
 . Guests will station their chairs in the parking lot outside the observato
 ry and knowledgeable docents with laser pointers will guide guests to the h
 idden secrets of the night sky. Expect to see double stars\, open star clus
 ters\, globular clusters\, maybe even a planet or two!<br><br>Please visit 
 <a href="https://rfo.simpletix.com" target="_blank">https://rfo.simpletix.c
 om</a> for important information and to buy tickets. You MUST have a ticket
  to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door. <strong>Pleas
 e note that tickets are non-refundable and cannot be used for future events
 . </strong></p><p>Cost is $35 per adult ($30 for seniors or under 18) and i
 ncludes the State Park parking fee.</p><p> </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250515T003059Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Bring Your Own Binoculars & Chair
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
