DESCRIPTION:SATURN... a world that continues to dazzle and mystify. This ic
 onic planet\, sixth from the Sun\, is home to an orbiting array of intrigui
 ng and unique worlds of its own. Come learn about this fascinating planetar
 y system and discover the autumn sky.&nbsp\;<br><br>Please visit <a href="w
 ww.rfo.simpletix.com">www.rfo.simpletix.com</a> for important information a
 nd to buy tickets. Seating is limited and you MUST have a ticket to attend 
 this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door.<br><br>Cost is $50 per a
 dult\, $40 for members\, and $45 for seniors or under 18 students and inclu
 des the State Park parking fee.
LAST-MODIFIED:20221104T045841Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Focus Night\, Saturn
