CREATED:20221116T181235Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u>As each month passes\, the sun &quot\;moves&quot\; to a 
 new sign of the zodiac\, and our evening sky reveals a new region of the un
 iverse for us to explore. This year we are offering a series of twelve even
 ings of exploration at RFO\, called &quot\;Your Universe&quot\;. Each month
  will be dedicated to a different zodiacal constellation\, its neighbors\, 
 planets\, prominent deep space objects\, and just enough astrophysics to br
 ing it together.<br><br>After the classroom program\, weather permitting\, 
 we will step out under beautiful dark skies to locate the constellations an
 d other objects discussed. Then we will move to RFO&#39\;s three main teles
 copes (an 8&quot\; refractor\, a 40&quot\; reflector\, and a 20&quot\; astr
 ophotography system) for deeper examinations. Sales are limited to 35 guest
 s so we can provide a more personal experience. You will have plenty of tim
 e at the telescope eyepieces\, and as always\, the observatory will be staf
 fed by knowledgeable and enthusiastic volunteers eager to show you the nigh
 t sights\, and answer any questions you may have.<br><br>Please join us for
  this year&#39\;s trip around the Sun and learn more about &quot\;Your Univ
 erse&quot\;.<br><br>$50.00 per adult\, $45 for students and seniors (62+) a
 nd $40 for members. Sugarloaf Ridge State Park parking fees are included.<b
 r><br>Please visit <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.rfo.sim
 pletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1669054338251952&amp\;us
 g=AOvVaw3LKFasL4LqfaNCBwjk0k3L" target="_blank">www.rfo.simpletix.com</a> f
 or important information and to buy tickets. Seating is limited and you MUS
 T have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door
 .<br><br><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20221116T181235Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
