CREATED:20251125T232812Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><i>Celebrate the longest day—and brightest night—of the year
 !</i></p><p>Welcome summer with an unforgettable evening under the stars at
  the <b>Robert Ferguson Observatory’s Summer Solstice Soirée</b>! Join us a
 s we celebrate the turning of the season with good company\, twilight views
  of the Sonoma hills\, and a night of celestial discovery.</p><p>As the sun
  sets on the longest day of the year\, enjoy summertime treats and the warm
  glow of golden hour at Sugarloaf Ridge State Park. Once darkness falls\, o
 ur observatory telescopes will open for guided viewing of the night sky—fea
 turing planets\, star clusters\, and deep-sky wonders. Our astronomers and 
 docents will be on hand to share insights about the solstice\, the science 
 behind it\, and its significance across cultures.</p><p>Come for the sunset
 \, stay for the starlight\, and celebrate the beauty of our shared skies.</
 p><p>Space is limited ~ register at <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com">rfo.
 simpletix.com</a>.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251125T232813Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Summer Solstice Soirée
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
