DESCRIPTION:<br><b>This event has been cancelled to to unhealthy levels of 
 smoke at RFO.</b><b><br></b><br>If you have purchased tickets for this even
 t please check your email.<br><br>_____<br><br>SATURN... a world that conti
 nues to dazzle and mystify. This iconic planet\, sixth from the Sun\, is ho
 me to an orbiting array of intriguing and unique worlds of its own. Come le
 arn about this fascinating planetary system and discover the summer sky.<br
 ><br>This is an outdoor event -- the observatory and its telescopes will NO
 T be available. Guests are encouraged to bring their own binoculars\, warm 
 clothing and chairs which will be stationed at socially distanced locations
  in the observatory parking lot. We will host an outdoor presentation on th
 e wonders of Saturn\, followed by a laser guided tour of the sky and comput
 erized telescope viewing of Saturn and other celestial delights.<br><br>Ple
 ase visit <a href="https://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/4728914">Brown P
 aper Tickets</a> for important information and to buy tickets. You MUST hav
 e a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door.<br>
 <br>Cost is $25 per adult ($20 for seniors or under 18) and includes the St
 ate Park parking fee.
