UID:1oaq0q106d8p302o67nd4lbpst@google.com
CREATED:20241031T023510Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us for an unforgettable evening of stargazing\, explora
 tion\, and cozy treats at Cosmos and Cocoa! This event brings together the 
 wonders of the cosmos with a warm cup of cocoa.</p><p>Kick off the night wi
 th a short\, guided hike along a portion our captivating Planet Walk\, wher
 e you'll encounter scale models of many of our solar system’s planets\, eac
 h with its own unique story. As the stars begin to sparkle\, we’ll gather f
 or an in-depth stargazing and storytelling session led by experienced astro
 nomers who’ll point out constellations\, planets\, and celestial objects. <
 /p><p>The event’s highlight is telescope viewing through our powerful obser
 vatory telescopes\, providing a chance to get up-close views of the astrono
 mical objects visible in the sky that month which could include the Moon’s 
 craters\, Saturn’s rings\, Jupiter’s moons\, and distant galaxies. Experts 
 will be on hand to answer questions and guide you through the night sky’s b
 est features.</p><p>And of course\, stay warm with complimentary cups of ri
 ch cocoa as you marvel at the universe above. Whether you're an avid starga
 zer or a curious beginner\, Cosmos and Cocoa promises an evening filled wit
 h wonder and warmth.</p><p>No prior experience necessary\, and all ages are
  welcome. Dress warmly and bring a flashlight with a red light setting (no 
 white light allowed). Red light flashlights will also be available for purc
 hase.</p><p> Register at <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com">rfo.simpletix.c
 om</a>. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241031T023510Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cosmos & Cocoa
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20240106T030000Z
DTEND:20240106T060000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:20d7as0ld1rkd25c7j3aa0lq2r@google.com
CREATED:20231127T082555Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><u></u>Have you ever wondered what&#39\;s really 
 out there in the night sky? Wished you could zoom in on cosmic marvels? Wha
 t if you had a handful of astronomers at your elbow\, showing the way\, ans
 wering your questions in plain language? That&#39\;s a Focus Night at the R
 obert Ferguson Observatory! These are small groups so you get plenty of sco
 pe time\, and a chance to focus on Jupiter\, the largest planet in our sola
 r system! Learn about the Great Red Spot\, the four Galilean moons\, missio
 ns to Jupiter\, and much more.<br> <br>If you&#39\;ve never seen Jupiter in
  a telescope\, you&#39\;re missing out on the thrill of a lifetime. But tha
 t&#39\;s not all! Other spectacles of the night sky\, including nebulae and
  galaxies\, also await.<br> <br>The program starts promptly at 7:00 PM. Aft
 erward\, weather permitting\, we will move to two of  RFO&#39\;s telescopes
  (an 8&quot\; refractor and a 40&quot\; reflector) for a deeper exploration
 . Sales are limited to 40 guests so we can provide a more personal experien
 ce. You&#39\;ll have plenty of time at the telescope eyepieces\, and as alw
 ays\, the observatory will be staffed by knowledgeable and enthusiastic vol
 unteers eager to show you the night sights\, and answer any questions you m
 ay have.<br><br>The program begins promptly at 7:00 pm. Allow generous time
  to arrive and park.<br><br>$50.00 per adult\, $45.00 for seniors (62+) and
  students\, and $40 for members. Cost includes the Sugarloaf Ridge State Pa
 rk parking fee.<br> <br>You MUST have a ticket to attend this event.  Atten
 dance is limited. Please note that tickets are non-refundable and cannot be
  used for future events. <br><br>RFO is operated by the Valley of the Moon 
 Observatory Association\, a 501(3)(c) nonprofit organization\, and all of t
 he proceeds will go towards maintaining this beloved Sonoma county institut
 ion.<br><u></u><br>Please visit <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http:
 //www.rfo.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=17003274049
 21525&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0okDJohbfJ6l_1SbKpyduO" target="_blank">www.rfo.simple
 tix.com</a> for important information and to buy tickets. Seating is limite
 d and you MUST have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sol
 d at the door.<br><br><br><u></u><u></u><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231127T082555Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Focus Night: Jupiter
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
