DESCRIPTION:Sip hot spiced cider\, enjoy festive treats\, and take part in 
 a variety of autumn-inspired activities before heading outside to explore t
 he night sky through our telescopes.<br><br>Our Docent and Member Parties c
 elebrate community\, curiosity\, and the joy of gathering under the stars. 
 Activities vary from year to year\, so you might find yourself painting a p
 umpkin\, or hunting for planets in a themed observatory scavenger hunt\, or
  simply relaxing with cider and cookies in costume alongside your fellow st
 argazers.<br><br>Come for a tour\, meet our volunteers\, ask questions\, an
 d enjoy an easygoing evening under the stars dedicated to the people who he
 lp RFO thrive.<br> <br>Not yet a member? You can sign up for membership her
 e: <a href="https://rfo.org/index.php/membership/">https://rfo.org/index.ph
 p/membership/</a><br><br>While this event is free to members and docents an
 d their families\, please sign up at <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com" tar
 get="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a> using your member code so we know how ma
 ny people to expect. Thank you!<br><br>If there are additional questions\, 
 please email <a href="mailto:info@rfo.org" target="_blank">info@rfo.org</a>
 . Thank you\, and we look forward to seeing you at future events.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260112T184502Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
