UID:07ru90desocj7ftm0qt5hq30ql@google.com
CREATED:20220527T234540Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Do you have a telescope at home that you just don’t use beca
 use you’re not sure how it works? Or\, are you looking to purchase or upgra
 de a telescope but don’t know where to start? Then this class is for you! W
 e will start with educating you on how telescopes work\, the pros and cons 
 of different telescopes\, items to consider when purchasing\, or upgrading 
 a scope\, and the basics of telescope operations. You’ll also receive one-o
 n-one time with some of our knowledgeable docents who will assist you in op
 erating your scope and can also show you what they can see through their ow
 n personal telescopes. Bringing a telescope is not required\, but if you pl
 an to do so\, please email Stephanie at <a href="mailto:sd@rfo.org" target=
 "_blank">sd@rfo.org</a> to inform her what type of scope you are bringing p
 rior to the event so we can be best prepared to help you.  </p><p>You MUST 
 have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door. 
 Purchase tickets at: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://rfo.simpl
 etix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1654127059719829&amp\;usg=
 AOvVaw1EPO4zG1CNIsHORuFNrdnR" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a> </p><p>
 Cost is $25 per adult\, $20 for seniors 62+ and $20 for students. $50 for f
 amilies from the same household. A $10 per vehicle State Park parking fee i
 s also required. If coming with a family\, please email <a href="mailto:sd@
 rfo.org" target="_blank">sd@rfo.org</a> and indicate how many adults and ho
 w many children are in your party. </p><p> </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220527T234617Z
