X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20250913T023000Z
DTEND:20250913T053000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:1i18kpitel9iuhf0qeud6iqos8@google.com
CREATED:20241018T210509Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><p>Do you have a telescope at home that you just don’t u
 se because you’re not sure how it works? Or\, are you looking to purchase o
 r upgrade a telescope but don’t know where to start? Then this class is for
  you! We will start with educating you on how telescopes work\, the pros an
 d cons of different telescopes\, items to consider when purchasing\, or upg
 rading a scope\, and the basics of telescope operations. You’ll also receiv
 e one-on-one time with some of our knowledgeable docents who will assist yo
 u in operating your scope and can also show you what they can see through t
 heir own personal telescopes. Bringing a telescope is not required\, but if
  you plan to do so\, please email Stephanie at <a href="mailto:sd@rfo.org" 
 target="_blank">sd@rfo.org</a> to inform her what type of scope you are bri
 nging prior to the event so we can be best prepared to help you.  </p><p>Yo
 u MUST have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the
  door. Purchase tickets at: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://rf
 o.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1729717011193191&am
 p\;usg=AOvVaw2VGCNrrenTJi79-glM9l9b" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a> 
 </p><p> </p><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20241018T210509Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Bring your own Telescope class
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20250307T023000Z
DTEND:20250307T043000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:7565hqv5n96cu32ftla538lk7o@google.com
CREATED:20241024T172252Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Have you ever admired amazing deep sky astrophotography imag
 es and wondered if you could ever create similar images?  Now you can!   </
 p><p>With raw data provided from the telescopes at the Robert Ferguson Obse
 rvatory\, in this class series of three sessions you will have the opportun
 ity to learn how to process and edit your own beautiful deep sky images. <s
 trong>Please note\, this workshop is meant as a 3-class series. It is highl
 y recommended to purchase tickets for all three days.</strong></p><p><stron
 g>Please note\, this is a virtual class. A Zoom link will be sent to partic
 ipants prior to the class.</strong> </p><p>What you will learn in this clas
 s:</p><p>- The fundamentals of Deep Sky Astrophotography</p><p>- An overvie
 w of image capture techniques (a dedicated\, hands-on class on Deep sky ima
 ge capture using your own equipment will be held later in Spring 2025)</p><
 p>- Robert Ferguson Observatory Image capture techniques - how we captured 
 the data that will be used in this class.</p><p>- An overview of image proc
 essing techniques</p><p>- An introduction to Siril\, a free and open-source
  Astronomical Image Processing Program</p><p>- A hands-on session where you
  will process data collected at the Robert Ferguson Observatory </p><p>- A 
 wrap-up session where you will have the opportunity to share and discuss yo
 ur images with other class attendees</p><p> </p><p>Class Prerequisites:</p>
 <p>- A computer newer than 5-years old (the newer the better)\, loaded with
  the latest operating system</p><p>- At least 8MB of RAM (more is better)</
 p><p>- At least 50GB of free disk space (preferably a solid-state disk driv
 e.  More storage is better)</p><p>- Familiarity with creating directories\,
  moving files between folders\, setting folder and file permissions\, and a
 ccessing cloud drives.</p><p><br></p><p>Get more information and purchase t
 ickets at <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://rfo.simpletix.com&am
 p\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1730222559537053&amp\;usg=AOvVaw0NJ9p
 Ht2qRqLlGC_ETuSip" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a>.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250117T162603Z
