DTEND:20221019T053000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:4uq7gniegar9p80c84hjlbs91b@google.com
CREATED:20220415T174438Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>This is a series of six classes and are designed for everyon
 e from total beginners to experienced amateur observers. Whether you want t
 o learn the constellations or have a telescope and want to expand your know
 ledge of viewing objects\, these classes have something for you.</p><p>The 
 focus is on learning the night sky in a &quot\;geographic&quot\; sense...lo
 cating yourself in our solar system\, our Milky Way and our local galaxy cl
 uster neighborhoods! A few constellations are introduced in each class—thei
 r myths\, history and interesting stars. We also cover deep sky objects suc
 h as the beautiful nebulae and clusters that never cease to awe and amaze.<
 /p><p>After each class (sky conditions permitting)\, we go outside to locat
 e the constellations just presented. We then move to the Observatory&#39\;s
  telescopes to view objects within the featured constellations.</p><p>Pleas
 e visit <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://rfo.simpletix.com&amp\
 ;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1650476464509228&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2VLbJTB
 Be5yR60GlTVlkFG" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a> for important inform
 ation and to buy tickets. Advance purchase is highly recommended and space 
 is limited\, though tickets can be purchased at the door if space is availa
 ble.<br><br>Cost is $25 per session or $80 for the entire series. </p><p>* 
  Please note: this class will be offered only if health safety protocols pe
 rmit indoor events.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20220415T174438Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Night Sky Class\, Session 3 of 6
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20250214T023000Z
DTEND:20250214T043000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:0g5bb824jbv7iv3mt26cv753f1@google.com
CREATED:20241007T065916Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Have you ever admired amazing deep sky astrophotography imag
 es and wondered if you could ever create similar images?  Now you can!   </
 p><p>With raw data provided from the telescopes at the Robert Ferguson Obse
 rvatory\, in this class series of three sessions you will have the opportun
 ity to learn how to process and edit your own beautiful deep sky images. <s
 trong>Please note\, this workshop is meant as a 3-class series. It is highl
 y recommended to purchase tickets for all three days.</strong></p><p><stron
 g>Please note\, this is a virtual class. A Zoom link will be sent to partic
 ipants prior to the class.</strong> </p><p>What you will learn in this clas
 s:</p><p>- The fundamentals of Deep Sky Astrophotography</p><p>- An overvie
 w of image capture techniques (a dedicated\, hands-on class on Deep sky ima
 ge capture using your own equipment will be held later in Spring 2025)</p><
 p>- Robert Ferguson Observatory Image capture techniques - how we captured 
 the data that will be used in this class.</p><p>- An overview of image proc
 essing techniques</p><p>- An introduction to Siril\, a free and open-source
  Astronomical Image Processing Program</p><p>- A hands-on session where you
  will process data collected at the Robert Ferguson Observatory </p><p>- A 
 wrap-up session where you will have the opportunity to share and discuss yo
 ur images with other class attendees</p><p> </p><p>Class Prerequisites:</p>
 <p>- A computer newer than 5-years old (the newer the better)\, loaded with
  the latest operating system</p><p>- At least 8MB of RAM (more is better)</
 p><p>- At least 50GB of free disk space (preferably a solid-state disk driv
 e.  More storage is better)</p><p>- Familiarity with creating directories\,
  moving files between folders\, setting folder and file permissions\, and a
 ccessing cloud drives.</p><p><br></p><p>Get more information and purchase t
 ickets at <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com">rfo.simpletix.com</a>.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250117T162544Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Deep Sky Astrophotography Processing class (class 1 of 3)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20260607T033000Z
DTEND:20260607T053000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:5v2udbrsemvu5i4f0q0grn8mno@google.com
CREATED:20250930T031155Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>¡Ven a conocer más acerca de nuestro universo! Los docentes 
 del Observatorio Robert Ferguson (ubicado dentro de Sugarloaf Ridge State P
 ark) nos guiarán en una charla astronómica bilingüe y en el uso de telescop
 ios para que tu y tu familia puedan observar el cosmos. El evento comenzará
  a las &lt\;8:30&gt\; pm en el aula del Observatorio con una presentación.<
 /p><p><a href="https://www.simpletix.com/e/senderos-rfo-observaci%C3%B3n-de
 -estrellas-2025-tickets-190476" target="_blank">Entradas</a></p><p>La admis
 ión es $10 para adultos\, $5 para jóvenes entre 12 y 18 años (deben ser aco
 mpañados por un padre de familia o guardián legal)\, y gratis para menores 
 de 12 años. Obtén tus boletos en <a href="https://www.simpletix.com/e/sende
 ros-rfo-observaci%C3%B3n-de-estrellas-2025-tickets-190476" target="_blank">
 rfo.simpletix.com</a> Si posees una tarjeta de EBT\, el dueño y tres famili
 ares pueden registrarse por gratis a través del programa <a href="https://m
 useums4all.org/about/" target="_blank">Museums for All</a>. Regístrate por 
 adelantado ya que el espacio es limitado y se llenará pronto. Recomendamos 
 vestirse en capas\, traer agua\, una linterna pequeña de mano (sólamente pa
 ra aluzar el camino\; no puede ser usada cerca del Observatorio a menos que
  tenga un filtro rojo)  y si la tienes\, una guía a las estrellas. Nos reun
 iremos en el estacionamiento del Granero Blanco. El estacionamiento\, usual
 mente $10\, es gratis para este evento.  </p><p>Para más información\, mand
 a un correo electrónico a Alma en <a href="mailto:senderos@sonomaecologycen
 ter.org" target="_blank">senderos@sonomaecologycenter.<u></u>org</a> o llam
 a al 707-247-5767\, martes a sábado entre 9:00 am-5:00 pm. Condiciones lluv
 iosas cancelan el evento pero continuará en condiciones nubladas .</p><p><i
 >Facilidad de acceso</i>: el Observatorio Robert Ferguson se ubica dentro d
 e Sugarloaf Ridge State Park. El área de estacionarse cuenta con un espacio
  designado para camionetas que necesitan acceso y aunque no oficialmente\, 
 hay mucho estacionamiento que puede ser accesible en esa misma área y en el
  estacionamiento del granero blanco. Hay una rampa que oficialmente cumple 
 con los requerimientos de la Ley para Estadounidenses con Discapacidades (A
 DA) para ingresar al observatorio. El área de asentamiento en el aula princ
 ipal del observatorio está compuesto de sillas que fácilmente pueden movers
 e. Hay baños disponibles dentro del edificio\, incluyendo uno accesible. El
  telescopio de la sala oeste tiene una rampa portátil para alcanzar el ocul
 ar\, y el telescopio de la sala este es una pantalla grande instalada en la
  pared.  </p><p>Encuentra más oportunidades recreacionales a través del pro
 grama Senderos Naturales <a href="https://sugarloafpark.org/guia-a-los-send
 eros/senderos-naturales/" target="_blank">en ésta página</a>.<br>Para apren
 der más acerca de RFO\, visita <a href="http://rfo.org/" target="_blank">rf
 o.org</a>. Para más eventos en Sugarloaf\, visita <a href="http://sugarloaf
 park.org/events" target="_blank">sugarloafpark.org/events</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250930T031156Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Senderos & RFO: Observación de Estrellas
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20230312T040000Z
DTEND:20230312T060000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:255vf43s3olekb1pbka2laud6i@google.com
CREATED:20221104T042721Z
DESCRIPTION:Thank you for supporting the observatory! Please join us for an
  informal open house. Come for a tour\, meet docents\,  and check out our t
 elescopes! \n\nDrive past the Sugarloaf Ridge park entry kiosk and park in 
 the lot by the white barn.\n\nDo dress warmly\; telescope rooms are open to
  the night air and it gets cold.\n\nRed lights only at the observatory to p
 rotect night vision\; bring a red flashlight if you have one — or we'll giv
 e you some red cellophane to cover your white flashlight.\n\nWhile this eve
 nt is free to members and docents and their families\, please sign up at rf
 o.simpletix.com using your member code so we know how many people to expect
 . Thank you!\n\nIf there are additional questions\, please email info@rfo.o
 rg. Thank you\, and we look forward to seeing you at future events. 
LAST-MODIFIED:20230315T231301Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Docent and Member Night - CANCELLED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
