UID:8ukcvj5j9enq3tu68dj8mhndgo@google.com
CREATED:20250916T005645Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us for an unforgettable evening of stargazing\, explora
 tion\, and cozy treats at Cosmos and Cocoa! This event brings together the 
 wonders of the cosmos with a warm cup of cocoa.</p><p>Kick off the night wi
 th a short\, guided hike along a portion our captivating Planet Walk\, wher
 e you&#39\;ll encounter scale models of many of our solar system’s planets\
 , each with its own unique story. As the stars begin to sparkle\, we’ll gat
 her for an in-depth stargazing and storytelling session led by experienced 
 astronomers who’ll point out constellations\, planets\, and celestial objec
 ts. </p><p>The event’s highlight is telescope viewing through our powerful 
 observatory telescopes\, providing a chance to get up-close views of the as
 tronomical objects visible in the sky that month which could include the Mo
 on’s craters\, Saturn’s rings\, Jupiter’s moons\, and distant galaxies. Exp
 erts will be on hand to answer questions and guide you through the night sk
 y’s best features.</p><p>And of course\, stay warm with complimentary cups 
 of rich cocoa as you marvel at the universe above. Whether you&#39\;re an a
 vid stargazer or a curious beginner\, Cosmos and Cocoa promises an evening 
 filled with wonder and warmth.</p><p>No prior experience necessary\, and al
 l ages are welcome. Dress warmly and bring a flashlight with a red light se
 tting (no white light allowed). Red light flashlights will also be availabl
 e for purchase.</p><p> Register at <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=ht
 tp://rfo.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=173077430585
 7537&amp\;usg=AOvVaw36Isj1KDwVGC6uG1l06IHQ" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.c
 om</a>. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250916T005645Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cosmos & Cocoa
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
X-SOURCE-URL:https://rfo.org/index.php/calendar-of-events/
DTSTART:20240604T030000Z
DTEND:20240604T063000Z
DTSTAMP:20260406T031028Z
UID:0in7degg77vd6gmliobbbteg5j@google.com
CREATED:20231206T223130Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><p>Please visit <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=ht
 tp://rfo.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=170232855481
 3975&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3SGKm4LQwgu429wH-W8M5R" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.c
 om</a> for important information and to buy tickets. Advance purchase is re
 commended as space is limited. Tickets are available at the door only if sp
 ace is available.<br></p><p>This is a series of six classes and are designe
 d for everyone from total beginners to experienced amateur observers. Wheth
 er you want to learn the constellations or have a telescope and want to exp
 and your knowledge of viewing objects\, these classes have something for yo
 u.</p><p>The focus is on learning the night sky in a &quot\;geographic&quot
 \; sense...locating yourself in our solar system\, our Milky Way and our lo
 cal galaxy cluster neighborhoods! A few constellations are introduced in ea
 ch class—their myths\, history and interesting stars. We also cover deep sk
 y objects such as the beautiful nebulae and clusters that never cease to aw
 e and amaze.</p><p>After each class (sky conditions permitting)\, we go out
 side to locate the constellations just presented. We then move to the Obser
 vatory&#39\;s telescopes to view objects within the featured constellations
 .</p><p></p><br><u></u>
LAST-MODIFIED:20231206T223130Z
LOCATION:Robert Ferguson Observatory\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA 
 95452\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Night Sky Class\, Session 1 of 6
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
