DESCRIPTION:<html-blob><p>Do you have a telescope at home that you just don
 ’t use because you’re not sure how it works? Or\, are you looking to purcha
 se or upgrade a telescope but don’t know where to start? Then this class is
  for you! We will start with educating you on how telescopes work\, the pro
 s and cons of different telescopes\, items to consider when purchasing\, or
  upgrading a scope\, and the basics of telescope operations. You’ll also re
 ceive one-on-one time with some of our knowledgeable docents who will assis
 t you in operating your scope and can also show you what they can see throu
 gh their own personal telescopes. Bringing a telescope is not required\, bu
 t if you plan to do so\, please email Stephanie at <a href="mailto:sd@rfo.o
 rg">sd@rfo.org</a> to inform her what type of scope you are bringing prior 
 to the event so we can be best prepared to help you. &nbsp\;</p><p>You MUST
  have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the door.
  Purchase tickets at: <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com">rfo.simpletix.com<
