 averse Sonoma County at 9:22am\, with roughly 75-80% coverage! We will be o
 n-site in front of the observatory with scopes with solar filters\, to safe
 ly view the eclipse\, and will also be selling special solar eclipse glasse
 s! This is a free event\, but you do need to either use your annual pass or
  pay the daily parking pass at the Sugarloaf Ridge State Park kiosk.
