DESCRIPTION:<br><b>This event has been cancelled due to forecast conditions
 .</b><br>SATURN... a world that continues to dazzle and mystify. This iconi
 c planet\, sixth from the Sun\, is home to an orbiting array of intriguing 
 and unique worlds of its own. Come learn about this fascinating planetary s
 ystem and discover the summer sky.<br><br>This is an outdoor event -- the o
 bservatory and its telescopes will NOT be available. Guests are encouraged 
 to bring their own binoculars\, warm clothing and chairs which will be stat
 ioned at socially distanced locations in the observatory parking lot. We wi
 ll host an outdoor presentation on the wonders of Saturn\, followed by a la
 ser guided tour of the sky and computerized telescope viewing of Saturn and
  other celestial delights.<br><br>Please visit <a href="https://www.brownpa
 pertickets.com/event/4683265">Brown Paper Tickets</a> for important informa
 tion and to buy tickets. You MUST have a ticket to attend this event\; tick
 ets will not be sold at the door.<br><br>Cost is $25 per adult ($20 for sen
 iors or under 18) and includes the State Park parking fee.
