UID:5p2bva25sgjo8o9o7pllr1teaj@google.com
CREATED:20210510T211939Z
DESCRIPTION:Join RFO docent\, Dave Kensiski\, via Zoom for an informative p
 resentation covering "How big is BIG?"\n\nTo quote Douglas Adams and the Hi
 tchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy\, "Space is big. Really big."  But just how 
 big is it?  This talk aims to blow your mind by showing how big the univers
 e really is.  We start with our humble observatory and expand from there to
  expose to the mindbogglingly huge scale of the universe.\n \nDavid Kensisk
 i joined the Robert Ferguson Observatory board in 2014\, served as Presiden
 t\, and heads the RFO IT team\, responsible for the computer and network sy
 stems and telescope upgrades. He holds a BS in Computer Science\, is active
  with the Boy Scouts\, and holds a ham radio license (W6DLK). He can often 
 be found running the 40″ or 20” CCD telescope for RFO’s public and private 
 events. He works for Google and enjoys sharing his love of astronomy with t
 he public.\n\nPlease register for this event via rfo.simpletix.com.
LAST-MODIFIED:20210510T212058Z
LOCATION:online via Zoom
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:RFO Speaker Series: "How big is BIG" with Dave Kensiski
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
