UID:00fu83e3tpv69qq1kpik48pvhp@google.com
CREATED:20241021T200900Z
DESCRIPTION:Have some sweet treats and enjoy an astronomy trivia game befor
 e heading out to our telescopes! This informal open house is for our member
 s (and docents) only. Come for a tour\, meet docents\, ask questions\, and 
 have an enjoyable night under the stars! \n\nDrive past the Sugarloaf Ridge
  park entry kiosk and park in the lot by the white barn.\n\nDo dress warmly
 \; telescope rooms are open to the night air and it gets cold.\n\nRed light
 s only at the observatory to protect night vision\; bring a red flashlight 
 if you have one — or we'll give you some red cellophane to cover your white
  flashlight.\n\nWhile this event is free to members and docents and their f
 amilies\, please sign up at rfo.simpletix.com using your member code so we 
 know how many people to expect. Thank you!\n\nNot a member? You can sign up
  for membership here: https://rfo.org/index.php/membership/\n\nIf there are
  additional questions\, please email info@rfo.org. Thank you\, and we look 
 forward to seeing you at future events.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250428T232421Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Treats and Trivia ~ Docent and Member Night
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
