UID:6l4lfq0ii5q7je6f3acnkmg3je@google.com
CREATED:20251219T232610Z
DESCRIPTION:Count meteors with us on this special August night and you’ll l
 ikely see dozens of “shooting stars.” This summer delight is part of the Pe
 rseids\, our best known meteor shower. But what causes it\, and why does it
  occur at the same time each year? Even more intriguing\, what prompted its
  source comet to shift from an expected collision course with Earth? Come l
 earn about the friendly forces in our solar system and how they still give 
 us brilliant fireworks every August\, albeit from a safer distance.<br><br>
 This special Perseids Meteor Shower Watch Party is designed as a full\, imm
 ersive experience. Begin the evening heading out to the observatory's three
  main telescopes to explore planets\, star clusters\, and other summer nigh
 t highlights. Telescope viewing will conclude at 11:00 PM\, after which we 
 will turn our attention fully to the night sky\, reclining and watching met
 eors streak overhead as Perseid activity continues to build.<br><br>Partici
 pants are welcome to remain on the observatory grounds late into the night 
 for meteor watching. <br><br>Please note: Guests may stay on the grounds un
 til the event concludes at 3:00 AM\, overnight camping is not permitted unl
 ess you have a separate reservation with Sugarloaf Ridge State Park. Space 
 is limited to ensure a comfortable and engaging experience. <br><br>Ticket 
 Options<br>To accommodate different interests\, two ticket types are availa
 ble:<br>Full Experience Ticket includes telescope observing and late-night 
 meteor watching.<br>Entry time: 9:00 PM<br><br>Observing and Meteor Watch T
 icket includes late-night meteor watching only.<br>Entry time: 10:30 PM<br>
 <br>Register at <a href="http://rfo.simpletix.com">rfo.simpletix.com</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260112T190718Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Public Perseids Watch Party 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Robert Ferguson Observatory
