CREATED:20220404T063826Z
DESCRIPTION:<u></u><u></u><p>Please visit <a href="https://www.google.com/u
 rl?q=http://rfo.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=16494
 86275781947&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2RWQlxBGTqCxanjHOf12ZF" target="_blank">rfo.simp
 letix.com</a> for important information and to buy tickets. Advance purchas
 e is required and space is limited.<br></p><p>This is a series of six class
 es and are designed for everyone from total beginners to experienced amateu
 r observers. Whether you want to learn the constellations or have a telesco
 pe and want to expand your knowledge of viewing objects\, these classes hav
 e something for you.</p><p>The focus is on learning the night sky in a &quo
 t\;geographic&quot\; sense...locating yourself in our solar system\, our Mi
 lky Way and our local galaxy cluster neighborhoods! A few constellations ar
 e introduced in each class—their myths\, history and interesting stars. We 
 also cover deep sky objects such as the beautiful nebulae and clusters that
  never cease to awe and amaze.</p><p>After each class (sky conditions permi
 tting)\, we go outside to locate the constellations just presented. We then
  move to the Observatory&#39\;s telescopes to view objects within the featu
 red constellations.</p><p><br><br>Cost is $25 per session or $80 for the en
 tire series.  </p><u></u><u></u>
