DESCRIPTION:<u></u><p>Do you have a telescope at home that you just don’t u
 se because you’re not sure how it works? Or\, are you looking to purchase o
 r upgrade a telescope but don’t know where to start? Then this class is for
  you! We will start with educating you on how telescopes work\, the pros an
 d cons of different telescopes\, items to consider when purchasing\, or upg
 rading a scope\, and the basics of telescope operations. You’ll also receiv
 e one-on-one time with some of our knowledgeable docents who will assist yo
 u in operating your scope and can also show you what they can see through t
 heir own personal telescopes. Bringing a telescope is not required\, but if
  you plan to do so\, please email Stephanie at <a href="mailto:sd@rfo.org" 
 target="_blank">sd@rfo.org</a> to inform her what type of scope you are bri
 nging prior to the event so we can be best prepared to help you.  </p><p>Yo
 u MUST have a ticket to attend this event\; tickets will not be sold at the
  door. Purchase tickets at: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://rf
 o.simpletix.com&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;ust=1729717011193191&am
 p\;usg=AOvVaw2VGCNrrenTJi79-glM9l9b" target="_blank">rfo.simpletix.com</a> 
 </p><p> </p><u></u>
